## AI Summary

One-paragraph explanation of why the AI created this spec (per Goal 1). What requirement was the starting point; what scope was set; what handoffs to other agents are expected.

## 1. Business context

Background. What customer need this feature addresses. References to the source RFP / requirements doc.

## 2. Personas

Numbered. One sub-section per persona involved.

### 2.1 {Persona Name}
- Role
- Pain point this feature addresses
- Success criteria from their perspective

## 3. Functional requirements

Numbered FR-NN. Each FR has acceptance-criteria sub-bullets.

### FR-01 {short title}
{description}

**Acceptance criteria:**
- AC-01.1 ...
- AC-01.2 ...

### FR-02 ...

## 4. Non-functional requirements

Per `agents/{a}/constitution/02-nfr.md` shape. Override the project defaults if this feature has stricter / looser targets.

## 5. Multilingual considerations

Per `projects/{p}/project.config.yaml multilingual.*`. Skip if multilingual is not in scope for any of this agent's channels.

## 6. Security

Privilege deltas vs the platform baseline. Audit / sensitive data / hierarchy changes.

## 7. Out of scope (explicit)

What this feature does NOT include. Numbered for traceability.

- OOS-01 {what} — reason
- OOS-02 ...

## 8. Open questions

Unresolved items. Number them; `/clarify` triages them at plan time.

- OQ-01 ...
- OQ-02 ...

## 9. Cross-feature impact

Read from existing specs in this agent's `projects/{p}/{agent}/features/` folder. Which prior features does this one extend / depend on / potentially conflict with.

